# UI Vision Sync

When a meaningful product feature is added, removed, deferred, reprioritized, or materially changed in Jira, docs, or code, check whether `docs/implementation/ui_vision.md` needs an update.

Run this check for:

- New or changed WEL Epics, Stories, Tasks, or Spikes that affect user-facing behavior
- Changes to `docs/feature-backlog/`, `docs/workflows/`, `docs/system-design/`, `docs/safety/`, or `docs/decisions/`
- Code changes that expose a new user-facing surface, API-backed capability, workflow state, share/grant behavior, safety obligation, or evidence/provenance display requirement

If the change affects UI direction, update `docs/implementation/ui_vision.md` in the same logical work:

- Add or revise the relevant feature/functionality sketch
- Update Source Basis or Jira references when needed
- Update phasing if MVP, near-term, post-MVP, deferred, or gated status changed
- Preserve WellBe's guardrails: personal-first, user-controlled, source-linked, non-diagnostic, calm, and grant-scoped

Do not silently add institution-first, clinician-controlled, cross-patient, or diagnostic UI framing. If a feature conflicts with the vision guardrails or a bible file, trigger the doc governance protocol before editing.
